Political capital: Hungarian guard increases state risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded this August with the support of the "Movement for a Better Hungary", have increased the risk of Hungary and the region in several ways.
In connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is "the exacerbation of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic clashes in the short term".
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provoking such a dispute, according to the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of political leaders: "public figures have left the discussion of the Roma issue to representatives of radical political groups, who have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungary counterpart".
It is suspected that this would exacerbate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, favor extremities, and increase the likelihood of violent confrontations.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard, not least thanks to the tremendous attention from the domestic and foreign media, "have significantly damaged the image of Hungary abroad, particularly as regards confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember: Since autumn 2006, the reorganisation of radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary has been on the rise, so that since summer 2007 several organizations called "national self-defense associations" have been founded.
"These groups are common to each of them defining themselves as a civilian organization, while they openly boast about preparing their members for - sometimes armed - defense tasks (catastrophe protection, national defense, order protection), citing the inadequacy of the police, the army, or the state itself," it said.
And furthermore: all this is done according to that method which seeks to disguise various political aspirations based on the political and party apathy of the population as a bourgeois initiative.
The emphasis on the civil character and the form of association thus serve not only to circumvent legal hurdles that could arise in the course of registration in court - it is at the same time a political strategy.
As the analysis shows, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are also a risk-augmenting factor in relations with neighbouring countries.
In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited in several neighbouring states as a potential source of danger, so many ultranationalist politicians of certain neighbouring countries see in the emergence of the Hungarian Guard the confirmation of its own anti-Hungarian policy.
All of this has an impact on the political stability of the region,” he said.
From the point of view of the research institute, the founding of the Hungarian Guard is not a single phenomenon in Central-Eastern Europe, so the political risk for the entire region has grown.
As reported, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are comparable to those of the Bulgarian National Guard, whose establishment was announced in August 2007 by the far-right Bulgarian National Union (BNU).
