The talks of Baden, near Vienna, constituted the sixth and last negotiating session since the Troika had received an order from the UN last August for a new mediation.
Americans and Europeans expect their mediation contract to end on December 10.
The Russians, who had already blocked Kosovo's granting independence at the Security Council, insist on continuing negotiations beyond this deadline.
Russia was and remains advocate of a negotiated solution, a consensual solution, Botsane-Khartchenko said.
