C3 hosts the Lollapalooza Festival in Chicago and the Austin City Limits Music Festival.
Vineland, New Jersey, is a summer destination for camping holidays.
The festival will probably take place from August 8-10 on a 500-acre private farm about 40 minutes from Philadelphia.
The director of Festival Republic Melvin Benn, formerly known as Mean Fiddler, is one of the producers of the most prestigious festivals in the world.
In 1989, he took over the leadership of the Reading Festival in the United Kingdom, which attracts around 80,000 people each year.
In 1999, Melvin Benn added the Leeds Festival to his portfolio, and then, in 2006, Festival Republic created the Latitude Festival at Henham Park in Suffolk.
Since 2002, Melvin Benn, in his capacity as co-owner, has also taken care of the production, license concessions and organizational tasks of the Glastonbury Festival, which can now accommodate up to 177,500 people.
Charlie Jones of C3, who describes Glastonbury as the most inspiring event he has ever attended, says his company and that of Melvin Benn are working side by side to provide the area with a European-style festival event.
We have chosen Philadelphia as a market and are eagerly working with the Fairmount Park Commission to create a festival in downtown Philadelphia, says Charlie Jones.
We conducted negotiations with the city and the Commission was motivated and enthusiastic about this project.
“Unfortunately, we have been stuck in political debates about the current administration,” continues Charlie Jones.
"Fortunately, we were able to discuss with Melvin Benn and we are making preparations to create a great festival in an exceptional place that will ultimately benefit the population."
C3 Presents has revived the 2005 Lollapalooza Festival in Grand Park Chicago after profiling itself in the world of the festival together with the Austin City Limits Music Festival in 2002.
The two events each generated $9.8 million and $11.8 million in gross tax returns in 2007.
These two festivals take place in an urban environment.
“The European model by Melvin Benn is a rural festival, whereas ours is more likely to take place on urban green spaces,” says Charlie Jones.
"The aim is, in one way or another, to merge these two concepts together to convey at the same time the impression of a rural festival on the European and an urban one in the American way."
Vineland is about halfway between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
“The Vineland community, including the mayor, is taking the burden of this event with joy,” says Charlie Jones.
The latter refuses to disclose the terms of the agreement, but he confirms "that they are sufficiently interesting to invest in such an event and record a festival that hopefully will have a long life."
Charlie Jones says the festival’s recording capacity is “very large,” corresponding to about 80,000 people at the Bonnaroo Music Festival in Tennessee.
