Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible accident caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of production of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance policyholder.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to provide the corresponding compensation amount in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance policy composed of several factors, including age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accident, higher contribution payments are due.
For this reason, both over-25-year-olds and women have to pay less contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more often the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a whole range of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance-oriented, but also a price-oriented choice.
Under the age of 25, when choosing low-cost insurance, they encounter numerous obstacles, such as low driving practice and the young driver’s license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance coverage to take out full-cash insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full cover with deductible, so that the benefits of a full cover insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract involves that the customer has to pay part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s main representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to your car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under the age of 25, it is in your hands to reduce insurance costs; thus, your credit increases by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalties will depend on the company and its earnings.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to enter into a contract, due to the fact that as driving practice increases, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most sensible to opt for a full-cost insurance with deductible.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish manager of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the fear of the novice has been dispelled.
Nevertheless, in the case of a married customer who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out full-cash insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the relevant person also allows it.
On the part of insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full-cost insurance with deductible (for an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the case that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which only takes effect for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to set a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full-cost insurance with deductible (at an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance that only applies with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs, which require that a thorough selection be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
